Date: Mon 19 May 2014
From: H Joel Hutcheson <HJoel.Hutcheson@aphis.usda.gov> [edited]


re: Novel phlebovirus - Australia: (TS) ticks. ProMED-mail archive no. 20140516.2478214

The background statement in this posting has an error that was transferred from the original source, the journal "Emerging Infectious Diseases" (Wang J, et al. 2014), namely: "During an investigation of the outbreak, a previously unknown bunyavirus from the tick _Anaplasma phagocytophilum_ was identified as the causative agent of SFTS (4)." (Yu et al. 2011).

Please note that _Anaplasma_ is a genus used for a group of rickettsiales bacteria; the tick species involved (mentioned in Yu et al. 2011) was _Haemaphysalis longicornis_.

References:
Wang, Jianning, et al. Novel phlebovirus with zoonotic potential isolated from ticks, Australia. Emerg Infect Dis. 2014; 20: 1040-1043.
Yu, Xue-Jie, et al. Fever with thrombocytopenia associated with a novel bunyavirus in China. N Engl J Med. 2011; 364: 1523-1532.

